Kwale county government give free secondary education to all local students who join national schools. Speaking to the media on Wednesday, county Education executive Mangale Choforomodo said they have set aside funds from the bursary kit to cater for scholarships. Chiforomodo congratulated all the students who performed well in KCPE exams. “We are happy the candidates have given Kwale a good name. The county government will support all its students who will join national schools,” he said. He urged parents to prioritise girl-child education, saying its a thing of the past to discriminate against them.  Bethany Christian Academy was the best school at the Coast with a mean score of 417. The school’s Ruth Chaka was seventh nationally with 446 marks.